author: Nivedha sukumar
text: I ordered a phone skin online after reading all the hype in the reviews. I'm sure those positive reviews are from people who got their skins applied in the shop. The online orders are terrible. The fit, adhesive, and size for my phone model are all awful. I had planned to order one for my laptop after doing my phone, but given the quality, it's not even worth 100 rupees. The worst part is that they don't respond to customer complaints—they just disappear. I'm certain people who visited their shop had a different experience. So, please, when posting your review, mention whether it was an online order or an in-store purchase. And yes I got mine stuck in a mobile shop i dint do it myself. There is no response even after sending a video on how it looks . Pure wastage of 599 rupees.
